; 1743-1805: William Paley

* When we inspect a complex thing like a watch, we infer that it must have had a maker; similarly, organisms must have a designer, and that is God.
* Moral virtue is doing good to mankind, in obedience to the will of God, and for the sake of everlasting happiness.